  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): HEAD (commit: 08d05227303b8f0b7d9c203c7d942788df1cbc97)\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: GCE\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Windows 1803, Windows 1809\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\nHigh cpu usage on the Windows nodes:\r\n```\r\nPS C:\\> Get-Counter '\\Process(*)\\% Processor Time' | Select-Object -ExpandProperty countersamples| Select-Object -Property instancename, cookedvalue,path| ? {$.instanceName -notmatch \"^(idle|_total|system)$\"} | Sort-Object -Property cookedvalue -Descending| Select-Object -First 25| ft InstanceName,@{L='CPU';E={($.Cookedvalue/100/$env:NUMBER_OF_PROCESSORS).toString('P')}} -AutoSize\r\n\r\nInstanceName CPU\r\n------------ ---\r\npowershell   71.15%\r\npowershell   13.07%\r\npowershell   5.08%\r\npowershell   4.36%\r\nmsmpeng      2.90%\r\npowershell   2.90%\r\nservices     0.73%\r\nkubelet      0.00%\r\n```\r\n\r\nMultiple processes running `Get-NetAdapterStatistics`\r\n```\r\nPS C:\\> Get-WmiObject Win32_Process | Select-Object CommandLine | Select-String powershell\r\n\r\n@{CommandLine=powershell}\r\n@{CommandLine=powershell /c \" Get-NetAdapterStatistics | ConvertTo-Json\"}\r\n@{CommandLine=powershell /c \" Get-NetAdapterStatistics | ConvertTo-Json\"}\r\n@{CommandLine=powershell /c \" Get-NetAdapterStatistics | ConvertTo-Json\"}\r\n@{CommandLine=powershell /c \" Get-NetAdapterStatistics | ConvertTo-Json\"}\r\n```\r\nI can reproduce this reliably when creating windows 1803 or 1809 nodes in GCE. \r\n\r\nPR #70121 added support for network stats on Windows by calling `powershell /c Get-NetAdapterStatistics | ConvertTo-Json`. \r\nThis function will be called every time kubelet gets queried for stats (`/stats/summary`, `/metrics`). Monitoring agents usually call periodically (e.g., 10s, 60s), etc. Kubelet itself also queries this to perform important functions such as eviction. I patched kubelet to disable the network stats on Windows, and was able to verify that the patch fixed the issue.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure why `Get-NetAdapterStatistics` can be so slow and consuming so much CPU. @PatrickLang, @adelina-t have you seen this when testing on Azure. I assume the CI test job is using the latest kubelet binary with network stats.\r\n\r\nRegardless, we'd need to cache the information since users can easily overload kubelets/nodes by querying the stats. /cc @feiskyer \r\n\r\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-windows-bugs \r\n/cc @pjh @jingxu97 @mtaufen \r\n/cc @dashpole ",
